title: PPPP’s Muhammad Sagid wins PS-85 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Muhammad Sagid has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-85 Malir-II by securing 27,791 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pir Hafizullah of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 14,304 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 42.34%.
